ial; font-size:12pt">4.3</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">4.4</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td><td style="padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:451pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We have over 18,000 service charge payers. All are affected in some way by the introduction of Universal Credit.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Negative implications could affect us as landlords in two ways</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">: </span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Depreciation of lifts</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Cleaning of windows on the ground floor</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Current legisla</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">tion allows us to depreciate the cost of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> repairs and replacement of lifts</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Under revised </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">DWP guidance</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> this won’t continue to happen.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> The impact</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> means a potential annual loss of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">£550,000</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. Service charges could be increased to cover this, but with many resid</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ents affected by welfare changes, ultimately we’ll have to cover the loss through bad debt provision. This has</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> an adverse effect on our business plan and therefore our ability to build new homes. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In some flats, particularly high rise we have responsibility for window cleaning. DWP guidance says we will not be able to charge for cleaning relating to ground floor flats. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Significant timely and costly work has to be undertaken for us to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">change all lega</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">l agreements with residents’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. Without this residents will</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> be paying for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">services they don’t receive.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The guidance also fails to take account of the legal agreements with tenants, including leaseholders. These constrain the options available to both us</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and the tenant. Apportionments for charges are set out in leases and tenancy agreements.  It’s a contract to pay us charges due. So, those in flats will have to make their Universal Credit payment stretch further to cover the cost of non eligible charges </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">which they have no choice but to receive.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Ultimately as a landlord we’ll be at a financial loss as bad debt is incurred.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:27.5pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">5.0</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p></td><td style="padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:451pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Implications on </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">continued provision of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">TA</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:27.5pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">5.1</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">5.2</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">5.3</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">5.4</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">5.5</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">5.6</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">5.7</span></p></td><td style="padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:451pt"><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We’ve won national customer service awards demonstrating how passionate we are about our service</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to vulnerable clients in TA</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Financially it’s becoming more difficult to provide the service across all 18 areas. The changes to housing costs within the wel</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">fare system remain a huge concern to the future of us being able to house vulnerable homeless clients.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 36pt 5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Government are introducing direct payments within universal credit. The main aim is to empower residents to manage money, ensuring they understand ho</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">w working families budget when receiving a monthly salary. The Government tell us this will be a cost neutral exercise for them. What they haven’t considered is the full impact direct payments will have. Even though Government recognise Universal Credit mu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">st be designed to protect the financial position of landlords, d</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">irect payment to tenants still means landlords will have to take unacceptable risks on collecting rent. Many landlords will not take that risk, leading to less supply in the private rented </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">sec</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">tor and a higher B&amp;B bill/ cost to public purse. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Concern has already been stressed by many landlords that low income or vulnerable families will not pay rent.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> No families in temporary accommodation have been included in the UC pilots.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> If this happens ultimately these families will end up being evicted. As local authorities have a duty to find shelter for homeless families, their only option will be to place them in unsuitable and expensive B&amp;B. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Many aspects of Welfare reform make lea</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">sing temporary accommodation from the private sector no longer a financial viable option for many registered social landlords. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The supply of good quality temporary accommodation is reducing, especially in London &amp; the South where there’s a buoyant private</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> rental market. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> direct payment element </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">will not make </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the welfare reform policy cost neutral. Instead it will increase LA spend through </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Discretionary Housing Payments (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">DHP</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">or the general fund.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">If tenants do not pay their rent registered social landlo</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rds will incur higher bad debt. This will ultimately affect our credit scoring and ability to borrow/self fund in an environment where grant funding to build new affordable homes is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">disappearing. The</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> end result is registered social landlords will not build</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> much needed new homes, holding back the recovery of the economy even further.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We want to continue to provide this service which our L</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> partners value. But proposed changes to how TA is funded are making it increasingly difficult for us to retain lease</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s and continue to provide this service. Here’s a summary of the issues:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Viability of TA. We have no certainty on exemption from direct payments or management fee arrangements. Without exemption from direct payments we’re unable to guarantee rent to propert</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">y owners. Without certainty on management fees we’re unable to properly plan or budget. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Supply. The buoyant rental market makes it virtually impossible to renew or procure in London &amp;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> neighbouring boroughs. Open market rents outstrip what we can pay property owners, so there is little or no incentive for them to lease homes to us. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Affordability. The inclusion of the management fee in the nationwide rent caps means most TA homes will b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e unaffordable to residents in London boroughs. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">All these</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> issues ultimately point to an increased spend for the public purse on inappropriate bed and bedfast for vulnerable families.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:27.5pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">6.0</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">6.1</span></p></td><td style="padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:451pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Innovation to support discharge of duty into PRS</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The localism act allows local authorities to discharge the duty of homelessness into the private rented sector. Again we completely support this where families can support themselves. But from our experience there are many families who require </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a higher lev</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">el of management to help them sustain tenancies. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Experience also tells us many landlords require extra support to manage vulnerable client groups. Its no secret many private landlords already only accept working families.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:27.5pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">6.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">6.3</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td><td style="padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:451pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We’ve been working with one LA to provide good quality housing from the private sector to allow them to discharge duty of homeless clients on 12 month assured short hold tenancies. The LA </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">supports</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> us financially to manage the tenant, without financial detr</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">iment to the landlord.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">From year 2 the tenant has received enough support to know how to sustain their tenancy. The LA </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">removes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> financial support and we manage the letting as a private let with the owner. This removes the hassle for the landlord. Removes t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">he problem of failing tenancies and repeated homelessness and provides a stable long term home for a family.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:27.5pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">6.4</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="m