le="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td><td style="padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:451pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This only works with buy in and support from LA.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> A blanket approach of discharge into the PRS could lead to a ‘revolving door’ of homelessness for some families, again leading </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> higher B&amp;B bill/ cost to public purse. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Recommendations</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We reiterate that we agree in principle the aim of welfare reform /universal credit /direct payments – The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">unintended consequence of direct payments is likely to be higher costs to housing providers, negative impact on credit ratings and fewer new homes bu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ilt, as mentioned above. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:5pt 36pt 5pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We ask that any resident of a registered social landlord has the option to opt out of direct payment arrangements</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:5pt 36pt 5pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We ask </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">any resident housed through the homeless route or prevention of homeless route in temporary accommodati</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">on be exempt from direct payment arrangements.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:5pt 36pt 5pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We ask that t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">he management fee be agreed and regarded as a support cost not a benefit eligible rent cost. The management fee does not go to the landlord as rent</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:5pt 36pt 5pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We ask that r</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">en</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ts for Temporary Accommodation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> be excluded from the benefit cap</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:5pt 36pt 5pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We ask for f</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">lexibility on local housing allowance for the most vulnerable to ensure adequate supply in buoyant areas</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:5pt 36pt 5pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We ask for c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">larity on long term exclusion from direct payments for residents in Temporary Accommodation.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">If we and other providers are unable to continue to secure temporary accommodation, Local Authorities will have to use Bed and Breakfast accommodation more. This costs more, both to the public purse and in terms of impact on vulnerable homeless families.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">27 September 2013</span></p></td></tr><!--[if !supportMisalignedColumns]><tr style="height:0pt"><td style="width:27.5pt; border:none"></td><td style="width:451pt; border:none"></td></tr><![endif]--></table><p style="border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; padding-top:1pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">5</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>